SIMPLE: headquarters
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headquarters
<hw>Head"quar`ters</hw> <pr>(-kw⟦add⟧r`t⟦etil⟧rz)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[but sometimes used as a <pos>n. sing.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quarters or place of residence of any chief
officer, as the general in command of an army, or the head of a police
force; the place from which orders or instructions are issued; hence,
the center of authority or order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brain, which is the <qex>headquarters</qex>, or office, of
intelligence.</q> <rj><qau>Collier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The main office from which an organization such as a
commercial enterprise is managed; -- usually where the chief executive
officer works.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headrace</ent>⟦br⟧
